<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.51/196.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Hartman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-06T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1915—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s July 23, 5 p.m. Department waiting with interest reply of
                            Foreign Office regarding its attitude conditional flotation of loan.</p>
                        <pb facs="0472" n="356" xml:id="pg_356"/>
                        <p>For your information Cooper telegraphs from London in part as follows:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Have private information Government intends get Congress pass act
                                    authorizing Executive suspend payments until differences with
                                    railway company settled.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Can you confirm this?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>